---
description: Load core repo context before substantial work
alwaysApply: true
---

Before substantial implementation, refactoring, or architecture changes, inspect the main project context.

Read these files when present:
- README.md
- docs/architecture.md
- docs/PRD.md
- docs/deployment.md
- docs/security.md

Context rules:
- Use docs/architecture.md to understand boundaries, components, runtime, integrations, and deployment assumptions.
- Use docs/PRD.md to understand business intent, requirements, scope, and acceptance expectations.
- Use README.md to understand setup, scripts, and conventions.
- Check existing Docker files, package manifests, CI config, and nearby source files before changing patterns.

If docs are missing or stale:
- Follow the dominant implementation pattern already present in the repo.
- Prefer conservative changes and note any assumptions.
